<section xmlns:xi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude" xml:id="syllabus-ma311">
	<title>Syllabus</title>
		
	<introduction>
		<p>
			Carefully review every item of this syllabus. By taking this course, you are agreeing 
			to the polices laid out in this document. Let me know if you have any questions.  
		</p>
	</introduction>
	
	<subsection label="ma311-general-info">
		<title>General</title>

		<xi:include href="./syllabus/common/instructor-info.ptx" />

		<subsubsection label="ma311-course-info">
			<title>Course Information</title>
			<p>
				<dl>
					<li><title>Course Description</title>
						<p>
							Ordinary differential equations (ODEs); Applications; Laplace transforms; Systems of ODEs.
						</p>
					</li>
					<li><title>Meetings</title><p>Room: MH 413 on MWF 1100 - 1150</p></li>
					<li><title>Prerequisite</title><p>Grade of C or better in MA 124</p></li>
					<li><title>Department Head</title><p>COL Troy Siemers</p></li>
				</dl>
			</p>
		</subsubsection>
	</subsection>

	<subsection label="ma311-grades">
		<title>Grades &amp; Coursework</title>

		<subsubsection label="ma311-final-grade">
			<title>Final Grades</title>
			<p>
				Your final grade is determined by a combination of the following items:
				<ul>
					<li>Number of Core Topic Passes (# of Ps)</li>
					<li>Number of Secondary Topic Passes (# of Ps)</li>
					<li>Overall Homework Score (%)</li>
					<li>Final Exam Score (%)</li>
				</ul>
				The table below shows that the letter grade you will receive will come from the first row where <term>EVERY</term> requirement is met.
		
				<table component="web">
					<title>Minimum Requirements for Final Grades</title>
					<tabular bottom="minor" top="minor" left="minor" right="minor" halign="center">
						<col width="10%"/>
						<col width="15%"/>
						<col width="15%"/>
						<col width="15%"/>
						<col width="15%"/>
